2. **Perturbation Spectrum and Observational Consistency**
   Derive the power spectrum of curvature perturbations $\mathcal{P}_\zeta$ and tensor perturbations $\mathcal{P}_t$ by treating Bogoliubov modes as quantum fluctuations on the condensate background. Express the spectral index $n_s - 1$ and tensor-to-scalar ratio $r$ as functions of the feedback parameters $\gamma$ and $N_s$. Explicitly check if the model allows for the observed $n_s \approx 0.96$ and $r < 0.06$. If the model predicts $n_s > 1$, identify the physical mechanism (e.g., non-adiabaticity of the condensate) that could correct the tilt.

